text: Dominicans, are an ethnic group and nation native to Dominica. Most Dominicans are Afro-Dominicans who were brought during the slave trade. The remainder of the population are white Dominicans mostly of French stock, people from the India, and the Caribs.Dominica | Facts, Geography, History, & Points of Interest | Britannica ==References== Category:Ethnic groups in North America
title: Dominicans (Dominica)
